networking

Class SBMessage

  • java.lang.Object
    • experiment.SBMessage
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable

    public class SBMessage
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable

    An SBMessage is a message being transmitted between a SBServer and a SBClient. It encapsulates necessary information in a message, making parsing easier. Every SBMessage has a type and action. You can think of action as a subtype. It also has a timestamp representing the time this message being created, which is useful in some cases. SBMessage applies factory constructor design pattern, so you can set message fields in a way you feel most comfortable. For example, the following expression creates a conversation message:

     
 experiment.SBMessage msg = new networking.SBMessage()
         .setType(networking.Type.message)
         .setAction(networking.Action.send)
         .setSequence(sequence++)
         .setSender("Alice")
         .setReceiver("Bob")
         .setBody("Hey how are you doing?");

    For parsing, as long as you know message type and action, you know what fields are related and valid.

    There is a sequence number for each message. At the beginning, a client and a server decide the initial sequence number. For each of the following message pairs, sequence should be incremented by 1. This is useful when you have a lot of messages sent and want to figure out which message do all responses you receive from the server response to. The detail design is still under working.

    Type.message is a conversation message. It doesn't have an action. It should set receiver and body fields.

    Type.control is a general purpose message that is used to perform something. It uses action field to specify what exactly it wants to do. Currently it supports

    • Action.signup for user signup, with sender (for username) and body (for password) set;
    • Action.login for user login, with sender (for username) and body (for password) set;
    • Action.bye for user logoff, which doesn't need any fields
    • Action.userlist to acquire online user list.

    Type.info is a message sent by the server to tell client some information. Currently this type isn't being used.
